parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the driver is startled or loses control of the vehicle. It can also lead to unnecessary repair costs and downtime.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning
often while driving at moderate to high speeds
without any apparent reason or collision. In some cases
the airbag warning light comes on
and the airbag module is found to be defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag system can lead to inadequate protection in the event of a collision, increasing the risk of injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
and the system is found to have faulty wiring
high resistance
or other issues that prevent the airbags from deploying properly in the event of a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate airbag installation or design can lead to inadequate protection in the event of a collision, increasing the risk of injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag system is found to be incomplete or incorrectly installed
or the manufacturer's documentation is unclear or misleading about the airbag features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and decreased fuel efficiency. In some cases, it can also trigger other sensor failures, such as the oxygen sensor, coolant sensor, and mass airflow sensor.
symptoms: Engine misfires
loss of power
stalling
flashing check engine light
reduced acceleration
and bucking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can prevent normal functioning of many electrical systems, creating a fire hazard due to overheating of the switch assembly, melting of plastic housing, and damage to insulation and conductor wires.
symptoms: Failure of ignition switch prevents normal functioning of electrical systems
overheating of switch assembly
melting of plastic housing
and damage to insulation and conductor wires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuse card design defect can make it difficult or impossible for the owner to identify and correct blown fuses, potentially affecting critical vehicle systems and leading to safety issues.
symptoms: Fuse card contains indecipherable symbols
making it difficult or impossible to identify blown fuses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window regulator can cause the window to suddenly drop into the door panel, potentially leading to loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: The window drops into the door panel without warning
the window is hard to get back up
the window regulator fails
and the window falls into the window seal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause the vehicle to hesitate, stall, and lose power, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates
stalls
and loses power
the check engine light comes on
and the heater core fails.
